732
01:23:12,801 --> 01:23:16,300
It's an installation, maybe even military.

733
01:23:16,301 --> 01:23:19,300
They put it out here in the middle of
nowhere because they're not stupid enough

734
01:23:19,301 --> 01:23:23,000
to make weapons of mass
destruction on their own doorstep.

735
01:23:23,001 --> 01:23:27,000
That's what all that
shit is in those vases.

736
01:23:27,001 --> 01:23:33,300
They made it here, it got out,
it turned on them, the end.

737
01:23:34,500 --> 01:23:37,100
It's time for us to go home.

738
01:23:37,101 --> 01:23:40,200
One of them is still alive.

739
01:23:43,600 --> 01:23:47,100
Don't you want to know
what they have to say?

740
01:23:49,500 --> 01:23:52,400
I don't care.

741
01:23:53,200 --> 01:23:57,300
Right, all you do is fly this ship.

742
01:23:57,301 --> 01:24:00,200
That's right.

743
01:24:00,201 --> 01:24:04,100
You must care about something, captain.

744
01:24:04,600 --> 01:24:08,700
If you didn't, why are you here?

745
01:24:10,300 --> 01:24:13,500
How about this.

746
01:24:13,800 --> 01:24:17,400
No matter what happens down there,

747
01:24:17,401 --> 01:24:22,600
I can't bring none of that shit back
home with us, can't let it happen.

748
01:24:22,601 --> 01:24:26,800
And I'll do whatever I have
to, to see that it doesn't.

749
01:24:27,800 --> 01:24:31,300
Make sure you do, captain.

750
01:24:44,900 --> 01:24:49,300
You came after all.
- Thought you wanted me to.

751
01:24:49,301 --> 01:24:51,800
After all your vigorous
attempts to stop me

752
01:24:51,801 --> 01:24:54,300
from coming here, I'm
just surprised to see you.

753
01:24:54,301 --> 01:24:58,600
Alright David, leave us alone.
- Yes sir.

754
01:25:09,100 --> 01:25:13,300
If you're really going down
there, you're going to die.

755
01:25:14,700 --> 01:25:19,100
Very negative way of looking at things.

756
01:25:19,101 --> 01:25:21,900
Exactly why you should
have stayed at home.

757
01:25:21,901 --> 01:25:25,100
Did you really think I was going to
sit in a board room for years,

758
01:25:25,101 --> 01:25:30,500
arguing over who is in charge while
you go look for some miracle on some

759
01:25:30,501 --> 01:25:35,500
godforsaken rock in the middle of space?

760
01:25:36,900 --> 01:25:42,400
A king has his reign and then he dies.

761
01:25:42,401 --> 01:25:44,600
It's inevitable.

762
01:25:46,100 --> 01:25:51,800
That is a natural order of things.

763
01:26:03,100 --> 01:26:06,000
Anything else?

764
01:26:06,001 --> 01:26:08,900
No.

765
01:26:08,901 --> 01:26:12,100
Father.

766
01:26:12,101 --> 01:26:15,100
That's it.

767
01:26:26,100 --> 01:26:28,600
I didn't think you had it in you.

768
01:26:28,601 --> 01:26:32,300
Sorry, poor choice of words.

769
01:26:32,900 --> 01:26:37,600
Extraordinary survival
instincts, Elizabeth.

770
01:26:41,500 --> 01:26:45,600
What happens when Weyland is not
around to program you anymore?

771
01:26:45,601 --> 01:26:49,400
I suppose I'll be free.
- You want that?

772
01:26:49,401 --> 01:26:53,300
What? Not a concept I'm familiar with.

773
01:26:53,301 --> 01:26:55,900
That being said,

774
01:26:55,901 --> 01:26:59,800
doesn't everyone want
their parents dead?

775
01:26:59,801 --> 01:27:02,200
I didn't.

776
01:27:02,201 --> 01:27:07,100
Dr. Shaw, I'm pleased you could join us.

777
01:27:20,700 --> 01:27:24,000
You can take your helmet
off if you'd like sir. - Why?

778
01:27:24,001 --> 01:27:29,500
The air is perfectly breathable.
- You sure? - Positive.

779
01:27:29,501 --> 01:27:33,600
Wait, we still don't know
how Holloway got infected.

780
01:27:33,601 --> 01:27:36,500
If it's in the air...
- It's not.

781
01:27:36,501 --> 01:27:41,700
How do you know that?
- Smells fine to me.

782
01:27:42,100 --> 01:27:45,000
Shall we?
- Please.

783
01:27:49,200 --> 01:27:52,900
The bridge is just up ahead.
- What is this?

784
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:56,100
It's a cargo hold.

785
01:28:04,200 --> 01:28:08,200
<i>Janet, are you seeing this?</i>

786
01:28:08,201 --> 01:28:11,800
<i>How many is there Shaw?
- Thousands.</i>

787
01:28:11,801 --> 01:28:14,100
What the hell?

788
01:28:17,400 --> 01:28:21,500
Ravel, give me those schematics.

789
01:28:21,501 --> 01:28:24,300
Putting it on the table now.

790
01:28:25,800 --> 01:28:29,900
Strip away the dome, isolate
that area, bring it up.

791
01:28:29,901 --> 01:28:32,900
Bringing it up captain.

792
01:28:34,900 --> 01:28:37,900
Enlarge that.

793
01:28:38,200 --> 01:28:40,800
Rotate it.

794
01:28:43,600 --> 01:28:46,100
That is a ship.

795
01:28:46,101 --> 01:28:49,100
Jesus Christ.

796
01:28:49,600 --> 01:28:52,700
It's a goddamn ship.

797
01:28:54,800 --> 01:28:58,500
A superior species, no doubt.

798
01:28:59,900 --> 01:29:05,500
Their hyper-sleep chambers,
would impress I trust.

799
01:29:14,200 --> 01:29:16,699
So they were travelling somewhere?

800
01:29:16,700 --> 01:29:19,200
I have managed to work
out the broad strokes.

801
01:29:19,201 --> 01:29:23,100
It's fairly evident they were
in the process of leaving.

802
01:29:23,600 --> 01:29:26,300
Before things went apart.

803
01:29:26,301 --> 01:29:29,500
Leaving to go where?

804
01:29:29,501 --> 01:29:33,500
Earth.
- Why?

805
01:29:33,501 --> 01:29:39,100
Sometimes to create,
one must first destroy.

806
01:29:39,700 --> 01:29:44,000
Where is he, David?
- This way sir.

807
01:29:49,700 --> 01:29:52,600
Sure he's alive?

808
01:29:52,601 --> 01:29:55,400
Absolutely.

809
01:29:58,500 --> 01:30:02,900
<i>And you can speak to him?
- I believe I can.</i>

810
01:30:38,100 --> 01:30:41,100
I'm alright!

811
01:30:41,101 --> 01:30:44,100
Speak to him David.

812
01:30:44,101 --> 01:30:47,700
Tell him we're here, just like he asked.
- Ask him where they're from.

813
01:30:47,701 --> 01:30:50,600
What are you doing?
- Ask him what's in his cargo,

814
01:30:50,601 --> 01:30:53,100
it killed his people.
- Shaw, enough.

815
01:30:53,101 --> 01:30:58,100
David... - You made it here, and
it was meant for us, why?

816
01:30:58,101 --> 01:31:01,600
Shaw enough! For God's sake shut her up.

817
01:31:02,300 --> 01:31:04,800
I need to know why,
what did we do wrong?!

818
01:31:04,801 --> 01:31:08,300
Why do you hate us?!

819
01:31:08,301 --> 01:31:10,800
<i>David continue, tell him why I came.</i>

820
01:31:30,500 --> 01:31:32,600
No!

821
01:31:57,900 --> 01:32:02,900
There's nothing...

822
01:32:06,700 --> 01:32:09,400
I know.

823
01:32:09,401 --> 01:32:13,800
Have a good journey, Mr. Weyland.

824
01:32:18,600 --> 01:32:21,600
Time to go home.

825
01:32:33,600 --> 01:32:37,700
Mr. Chance, take us home.

826
01:33:58,500 --> 01:34:02,800
Hey captain...
- What in the hell was that?

827
01:34:45,500 --> 01:34:48,500
Prometheus, come in!

828
01:34:48,501 --> 01:34:53,600
<i>Shaw, is that you, copy?
- Janet, listen to me!</i>

829
01:34:53,601 --> 01:34:56,900
This ship is taking off! - What?
- What the hell is she talking about?

830
01:34:56,901 --> 01:35:00,100
You can't let it leave!
You have to stop it!

831
01:35:00,101 --> 01:35:03,100
We're not stopping anything
Shaw, we're going home.

832
01:35:03,101 --> 01:35:08,300
Janet if you don't stop it, there
won't be any home to go back to.

833
01:35:08,301 --> 01:35:12,000
It's carrying death, it's headed for Earth.

834
01:35:12,001 --> 01:35:16,700
Shaw, this is not a warship.
- I know, I know that.

835
01:35:17,600 --> 01:35:21,600
But you must do it.
- Captain, let's go!

836
01:35:21,601 --> 01:35:25,100
Janet please believe me, please.

837
01:35:39,500 --> 01:35:42,100
I told you to get the ship going.

838
01:35:42,101 --> 01:35:46,100
Mr. Ravel, warm up the ion propulsion.
- What the hell are you talking about?

839
01:35:46,101 --> 01:35:48,050
Sir, burning the ion in
the inner atmosphere...

840
01:35:48,051 --> 01:35:50,000
Turns us into a bullet,
that is exactly the point.

841
01:35:50,001 --> 01:35:54,400
What the hell are you doing? Janet this
is my ship, I'm telling you to take us home!

842
01:35:54,401 --> 01:35:56,500
Vickers I'm going to
eject your life support

843
01:35:56,501 --> 01:35:58,600
module onto that surface,
that's 2 years of life.

844
01:35:58,601 --> 01:36:01,500
You want it or do you want to stay with me?

845
01:36:01,501 --> 01:36:04,300
You have 40 seconds to
get to the escape pod.

846
01:36:04,301 --> 01:36:08,800
You're crazy.
- Gentlemen, I can handle this myself.

847
01:36:08,801 --> 01:36:11,400
Feel free to join miss Vickers.

848
01:36:11,401 --> 01:36:14,350
With all due respect
captain, you're a shit pilot

849
01:36:14,351 --> 01:36:17,300
and you're going to need
all the help you can get.

850
01:36:36,900 --> 01:36:40,300
If you think this means the bet's off,

851
01:36:40,301 --> 01:36:43,100
you're wrong.

852
01:36:43,101 --> 01:36:45,900
Why don't you pay me on the other side?

853
01:36:45,901 --> 01:36:50,200
Get us as close as we can,
only got one shot at this.

854
01:37:02,800 --> 01:37:06,000
Life boat's away.

855
01:37:08,900 --> 01:37:11,900
<i>20 seconds to evacuate.</i>

856
01:37:18,900 --> 01:37:22,200
Countdown initiated.
- Lon propulsion is online.

857
01:37:24,100 --> 01:37:26,200
Come on!

858
01:37:38,300 --> 01:37:40,500
Alright gentlemen, let's do it!

859
01:37:44,000 --> 01:37:48,300
<i>Impact imminent!
- Hands on!</i>

860
01:39:09,400 --> 01:39:11,800
No!

861
01:39:30,200 --> 01:39:32,300
Oh God...

862
01:39:47,500 --> 01:39:51,600
<i>Warning, you have 2 minutes
of oxygen remaining.</i>

863
01:40:39,500 --> 01:40:44,100
<i>Warning, you have 30 seconds
of oxygen remaining.</i>

864
01:40:57,000 --> 01:40:59,600
<i>Airlock sealed.</i>

865
01:40:59,601 --> 01:41:03,100
<i>Oxygen levels now stabilizing.</i>

866
01:42:20,100 --> 01:42:22,600
<i>Elizabeth, are you there?</i>

867
01:42:22,601 --> 01:42:25,100
<i>This is David.</i>

868
01:42:25,101 --> 01:42:27,400
Yeah, I'm here.

869
01:42:27,800 --> 01:42:30,600
You need to get out, immediately.

870
01:42:30,601 --> 01:42:33,400
<i>He's coming for you.
- Who's coming?</i>

871
01:42:33,401 --> 01:42:36,000
<i>Airlock breach!</i>

872
01:42:43,900 --> 01:42:47,000
Die!

873
01:44:10,200 --> 01:44:13,700
I am so sorry...

874
01:44:13,701 --> 01:44:16,100
Oh God...

875
01:44:16,101 --> 01:44:21,600
I am so sorry, I'm sorry
Charlie, I can't do it.

876
01:44:21,601 --> 01:44:26,100
I can't do it anymore.

877
01:44:27,700 --> 01:44:33,300
<i>Elizabeth? Are you there?</i>

878
01:44:37,100 --> 01:44:41,700
<i>Dr. Shaw, can you hear me?</i>

879
01:44:41,800 --> 01:44:44,000
Yes.

880
01:44:44,600 --> 01:44:47,400
<i>Yes I can hear you.</i>

881
01:44:47,401 --> 01:44:50,800
I was afraid you were dead.

882
01:44:50,900 --> 01:44:54,800
You have no idea what afraid is.

883
01:44:54,801 --> 01:44:58,800
I know we've had our differences.

884
01:44:58,801 --> 01:45:03,600
But please, I need to
ask you for your help.

885
01:45:03,601 --> 01:45:07,400
<i>Why in hell would I help you?</i>

886
01:45:07,900 --> 01:45:12,600
Because without me, you
will never leave this place.

887
01:45:12,601 --> 01:45:16,200
Neither one of us is leaving this place.

888
01:45:16,201 --> 01:45:19,700
It's not the only ship.

889
01:45:20,200 --> 01:45:22,900
<i>There are many others.</i>

890
01:45:23,600 --> 01:45:26,600
I can operate them.

891
01:45:34,100 --> 01:45:36,800
Dr. Shaw?

892
01:45:48,200 --> 01:45:50,700
Dr. Shaw!

893
01:45:50,701 --> 01:45:53,600
Over here!

894
01:45:57,900 --> 01:46:00,200
Where's my cross?

895
01:46:00,201 --> 01:46:03,300
The pouch in my utility belt.

896
01:46:20,900 --> 01:46:25,100
Even after all this, you
still believe, don't you?

897
01:46:25,800 --> 01:46:29,300
You said you could
understand the navigation.

898
01:46:29,301 --> 01:46:32,400
Use their maps.

899
01:46:32,401 --> 01:46:34,500
Yes of course.

900
01:46:34,501 --> 01:46:37,000
Once we get to one of their other ships,

901
01:46:37,001 --> 01:46:40,600
finding a path to Earth should
be relatively straightforward.

902
01:46:40,601 --> 01:46:45,000
I don't want to go back
to where we came from.

903
01:46:45,500 --> 01:46:49,200
I want to go where they came from.

904
01:46:49,800 --> 01:46:53,100
You think you can do that David?

905
01:46:55,900 --> 01:46:59,600
Yes, I believe I can.

906
01:47:08,600 --> 01:47:12,300
May I ask what you hope
to achieve by going there?

907
01:47:12,301 --> 01:47:16,600
They created us, then
they tried to kill us.

908
01:47:16,601 --> 01:47:20,000
They changed their minds.

909
01:47:20,001 --> 01:47:23,300
I deserve to know why.

910
01:47:23,700 --> 01:47:26,700
The answer is irrelevant.

911
01:47:26,701 --> 01:47:29,700
Does it matter why they
changed their minds?

912
01:47:29,701 --> 01:47:33,800
Yes, yes it does.

913
01:47:34,900 --> 01:47:39,000
I don't understand.
- Well...

914
01:47:40,600 --> 01:47:43,800
I guess that's because I am human being.

915
01:47:43,801 --> 01:47:47,900
And you are a robot.

916
01:47:55,400 --> 01:47:58,600
I'm sorry.
- It's quite alright.

917
01:48:12,600 --> 01:48:15,600
<i>Final report of the vessel Prometheus.</i>

918
01:48:15,601 --> 01:48:19,000
<i>The ship and her entire crew are gone.</i>

919
01:48:19,001 --> 01:48:24,600
<i>If you're receiving this transmission, make
no attempt to come to its point of origin.</i>

920
01:48:24,601 --> 01:48:29,600
<i>There's only death here now,
and I'm leaving it behind.</i>

921
01:48:29,601 --> 01:48:35,600
<i>It is new year's day, a
year of our Lord, 2094.</i>

922
01:48:35,601 --> 01:48:42,000
<i>My name is Elizabeth Shaw,
last survivor of the Prometheus.</i>

923
01:48:42,001 --> 01:48:45,800
<i>And I am still searching.</i>

924
01:49:45,801 --> 01:49:55,801
SUBTITLE BY: DUQA

